    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.85-86_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">85</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        271<del>t</del><add>6</add> Sinton Ave.,
                        Regina, Sask.,
                        Dec. 30, 1958.
                    </dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 8,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am writing a book on the Peyote religion, together with four Saskatchewan scientists, and would appreciate it very much if you would give me permission to quote from your book, <hi rend="underline">Black Elk Speaks: Being the Life Story of a Holy Man of the Ogalala Sioux.</hi></p>
                
                <p>I would like to quote Black Elk's prayer, with the incident that occurred at the time, when a few drops of rain fell; his first view of and feelings about the Ghost Dance, and the hunger of his people; and his story of the Ghost Dance massacre, making a total of about 1580 words.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes for the New Year for you and yours,</salute>
                
                    <salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>F. H. Kahan</signed> <!--Fannie Hoffer Kahan?-->
                    <signed>(Mrs.) F.H. Kahan.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.85-86_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">86</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Mrs. <hi rend="caps">F. H.</hi> Kahan,
                    2716 Sinton Ave.,
                    Regina, Saskatchewan,
                    Canada.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    REGINA SASK.
                    JAN 3
                    7 PM
                    1959
                    CANADA
                
                    FIGHT POLIO
                    JOIN SASKATCHEW<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">AN</unclear>
                    MARCH OF DIMES
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>5 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>EIIR EIIR
                    5¢ 5¢
                    POSTES CANADA POSTAGE</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 8,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">U.S.A.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <note type="recipient">
                    Ansd
                    1-10-59
                    $50
                </note>
                
            </div1>
